ceived` checks `conversationId != _currentConversationId`** - It returns early i
f the message is for a different conversation. But it doesn\'t notify the conver
sation list or show a notification. This is acceptable for MVP.\n\n20. **`match_
list_page.dart` now serves as conversation list** - The page title is "消息" (Me
ssages) and it uses `ConversationListCubit`. This is correct per the PRD.\n\n21.
**Design system `SwChatBubble` uses `DesignTokens.secondaryColor`** - According 
to `flutter.md`, `secondaryColor` is a legacy alias. But looking at the token gu
ide, it says "禁止在新代码中使用 Legacy aliases". `DesignTokens.secondaryColor` 
is listed as a legacy alias. This is a **Minor** issue.\n\nWait, let me re-read 
the token guide:\n- `DesignTokens.surfaceColor` is explicitly called out as a le
gacy alias.\n- `secondaryColor` is not explicitly listed in the table, but the t
able says "Legacy aliases: `tokens.dart` 中的别名，如 `surfaceColor = background
`". It doesn\'t list all aliases.\n\nLet me check what tokens exist. Actually, I
don\'t have `tokens.dart` content. Let me see if `secondaryColor` is mentioned a
nywhere.\n\nActually, looking at the widgetbook code, there are many uses of var
ious tokens. I\'ll note this as a potential issue if `secondaryColor` is indeed 
a legacy alias, but without reading `tokens.dart`, I can\'t be certain. Let me s
kip this or mark it as minor.\n\n22. **ImBloc `_messages` list grows unbounded**
- When loading messages multiple times, the list grows. When leaving a conversat
ion and entering a new one, `setCurrentConversation` is called but `_messages` i
s NOT cleared. This means messages from the previous conversation will still be 
there! Looking at `chat_page.dart`:\n\n```dart\n@override\nvoid initState() {\n 
super.initState();\n  final bloc = context.read<ImBloc>();\n  bloc.setCurrentCon
versation(widget.conversationId, widget.currentUserId);\n  // ...\n  bloc.add(Im
LoadMessages(conversationId: widget.conversationId));\n}\n```\n\nAnd in `ImBloc.
_onLoadMessages`:\n```dart\nif (event.cursor == null) {\n  _messages.clear();\n}
\n_messages.insertAll(0, result.items);\n```\n\nSo when loading the first page (
cursor == null), it clears. But what if the user navigates from conversation A t
o conversation B? In `app.dart`, a NEW `ImBloc` is created for each `ChatPage`. 
So when the user goes to a new chat, a new bloc is created. The old bloc is disp
osed. So this is actually fine because each chat page gets its own bloc.\n\n23. 
**ImBloc `_onMessageAck` doesn\'t handle missing temp message** - If the ack com
es back but the temp message was already removed, it just does nothing. Fine.\n\
n24. **`im.controller.ts` GET /messages doesn\'t validate conversation_id** - It
just checks `if (!conversationId)`. But `conversationId` is typed as `string`, s
o if it\'s an empty string `""`, `!conversationId` is true. But what if it\'s un
defined? The parameter is declared as `conversationId: string` without `?`, so N
estJS will require it. Actually, looking at the signature:\n```typescript\n@Quer
y("conversation_id") conversationId: string,\n```\nWithout `?`, NestJS doesn\'t 
enforce presence for query params. So `conversationId` could be `undefined` and 
the type annotation is wrong. But the check `if (!conversationId)` handles both 
`undefined` and empty string. This is acceptable.\n\n25. **`im.controller.ts` mi
ssing `@Query` validation DTOs** - The NestJS spec says "所有入参使用 class-vali
dator + class-transformer". For REST APIs, the controller should use DTOs with v
alidation. Instead, it manually parses limit. This is a **Major** code style/arc
hitecture issue.\n\n26. **`im.gateway.ts` `@MessageBody()` doesn\'t validate DTO
s** - For WebSocket, it uses `@MessageBody() dto: SendMessageDto` but there\'s n
o validation pipe applied. NestJS websockets don\'t automatically validate witho
ut `@UsePipes(new ValidationPipe())`. So invalid messages could pass through. Th
is is a **Major** issue.\n\n27. **`scripts/generate-types.sh` and `scripts/check
-contract-sync.sh` changes** - Need to verify these are correct.\n\n28. **`apps/
api/src/app.module.ts` changes** - Need to verify the IM module is registered.\n
\nLet me read a few more files to complete my review.',
